supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation throughout. Fols 55r-92v has another, contemporaneous, foliation: 210-217 and 237-266, suggesting that these leaves were part of a larger manuscript.

handDesc.handNote: The hand of ff. 55r-92v has been identified by Jón Helgason as belonging to the youngest son of the priest Jón Arason of Vatnsfjörður; Oddur Jónsson.

physDesc.additions: FF. 163v-16v are taken up by pen trials and the like.
